OL,4,C'Pervasive racism' blamed for failure
OL,5,Cto commemorate black and Asian troops
OL,6, Tens of thousands of predominantly
OL,7, black and Asian service personnel who
OL,8, died fighting for the British Empire
OL,9, were not properly commemorated due to
OL,10, "pervasive racism", a report has said.
OL,12,FThe Commonwealth War Graves Commission
OL,13,Fapologised after it found individuals
OL,14,Fwere not formally remembered in the
OL,15,Fsame way as white troops.
OL,17,F"The events of a century ago were wrong
OL,18,Fthen and are wrong now," it said.
OL,20,FDefence Secretary Ben Wallace will
OL,21,Faddress MPs about the findings later.
